=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Protect piperazine with Boc2O to give mono-Boc piperazine; Step 2: SNAr with 2-chloro-4-bromopyridine to install the 2-pyridyl group and retain the C4 bromide, affording tert-butyl 4-(4-bromopyridin-2-yl)piperazine-1-carboxylate; Step 3: In parallel, prepare 2-ethynyl-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridine from 2-bromo-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridine via Sonogashira coupling with TMS-acetylene, then desilylation; Step 4: Sonogashira couple the bromopyridine intermediate with 2-ethynyl-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridine to form the Boc-protected piperazine–pyridine–C#C–pyridine core; Step 5: Remove Boc with TFA, then mesylate the liberated piperazine nitrogen with MsCl/Et3N to furnish CS(=O)(=O)N1CCN(c2ccc(C#Cc3ccc(C(F)(F)F)cn3)cn2)CC1.

=== NORMALIZED STUDENT ANSWER ===
